<subSubSection id="AE4F1F04FDD7FE7185D83AB8DDFF7310" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="49715B8F59D6600C93248C4D3E0CE212" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="A5BB29CF28C89D283467E94152A4067B" LSID="767686A9-604A-5FB2-A1C7-2E6B6A4F5416" authority="C. L. Koch, 1835" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1835" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Xysticus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xysticus" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Xysticus C. L. Koch, 1835</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="747F0C08D549FDC83B01E1C4F9D96D74" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="comments">
<paragraph id="D66124C7E6679FFEBAAD5008EB1BF215" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E9D1929327790E39CF2F0402A39273FE" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicName id="76E36E69D049E2C73F6A3D8F76F1D859" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1835" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Xysticus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xysticus" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="03BA9E6EFE1CEAB3F4B9DB14B8F1CBB8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Xysticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the most diverse genera in 
<taxonomicName id="712AB154845BA90B3637C26768900FC5" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1833" class="Insecta" family="Thomisidae" genus="Thomisidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thomisidae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Thomisidae</taxonomicName>
with 293 named species (
<bibRefCitation id="3AC4E7AE18A10BF2E3F097A78444B14D" author="World Spider Catalog" journalOrPublisher="Oriental Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" publicationUrl="https://wsc.nmbe.ch/" refId="B24" refString="World Spider Catalog, 2022. World Spider Catalog. Natural History Museum Bern. Version 22.5. https://wsc.nmbe.ch/" title="World Spider Catalog. Natural History Museum Bern. Version 22.5." url="https://wsc.nmbe.ch/" year="2022">WSC 2022</bibRefCitation>
). Fifty-nine species are known from China. Of these, 19 are known only from females, and five from males. Most species are distributed in northern China and only one species, 
<taxonomicName id="5313545E562F84E704F1A444236B6A7C" authorityName="Schenkel" authorityYear="1963" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Xysticus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xysticus lesserti" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lesserti">
<emphasis id="CCD7FCDC0C17AB31F65949D1FC13E40A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Xysticus lesserti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Schenkel, 1963, is known from Guizhou Province (
<bibRefCitation id="7B9BA0BBB582F6E69BEB672C1BE9636B" author="Li, SQ" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" refId="B7" refString="Li, SQ, Lin, YC, 2016. Species Catalogue of China. Vol. 2. Animals. Invertebrates (1). Arachnida: Araneae. Science Press, Beijing" title="Species Catalogue of China. Vol. 2. Animals. Invertebrates (1). Arachnida: Araneae." year="2016">Li and Lin 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
